  keywords="scrabble premium squares, triple word score strategy, double letter score, TWS placement, scrabble multiplier stacking, premium square tactics"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Maximizing Premium Squares in Scrabble — DLS, DWS, TLS, TWS Tactics",
    "description": "Master premium square placement in Scrabble. Learn when to target DLS vs TWS, how to stack multipliers, and placement tactics for maximum scoring impact.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-30",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-premium-square-strategy" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many premium squares are on a Scrabble board?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A standard Scrabble board has 61 premium squares: 24 Double Letter Score (DLS), 17 Double Word Score (DWS), 12 Triple Letter Score (TLS), and 8 Triple Word Score (TWS). The centre star counts as a DWS for the opening play only." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the best tile to place on a Triple Letter Score?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Place your highest-value tile on the TLS. Z (10pts) on TLS = 30 points from one tile alone. Q (10pts) = 30, X (8pts) = 24, J (8pts) = 24. Always prioritise putting high-value tiles on letter multipliers." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can you hit two premium squares in one play in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. A word can cover multiple premium squares and all bonuses apply. The most powerful combination is hitting two TWS squares in one word (a triple-triple), which multiplies the word score by 9. A bingo across two TWS could score 500+ points." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Strategy</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Maximizing Premium Squares in Scrabble</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>6 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔍</span> Solver</a> <a href="/activities/#quiz" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎯</span> Quiz</a> <a href="/activities/#anagram" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔀</span> Anagram</a> <a href="/activities/#rack" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🎲</span> Rack</a> <a href="/activities/#wotd" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">📖</span> WOTD</a> <a href="/sixty-seconds/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">⏱️</span> 60s</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        The difference between a 300-point game and a 500-point game comes down to premium squares. Those coloured cells are score multipliers — and the players who consistently land high-value tiles on them dominate every game. Understanding which squares to target, when to sacrifice position for points, and how to stack multipliers separates good players from great ones.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">61</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Premium squares on board</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">×9</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Triple-triple multiplier</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWS squares (most valuable)</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Premium Square Types</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">DLS — Double Letter (×24)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Doubles one tile's value. Best for Z=20, Q=20, X=16, J=16 on this square.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
          <p class="text-purple-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">TLS — Triple Letter (×12)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Triples one tile. Z on TLS = 30pts from one tile alone. The biggest single-tile boost.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-pink-500/30 bg-pink-950/10">
          <p class="text-pink-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">DWS — Double Word (×17)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Doubles entire word after letter bonuses. Best with long, high-scoring words.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">TWS — Triple Word (×8)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Triples entire word. Only 8 exist. A 30-point word becomes 90. Most impactful squares.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Placement Tactics</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 The Golden Rule</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Put <span class="text-white font-medium">high-value tiles on letter multipliers</span> (TLS/DLS) and <span class="text-white font-medium">long words on word multipliers</span> (TWS/DWS). Z on a TLS in a word on TWS = devastating score.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">TLS + high tile = instant power:</span> Z (10pts) on TLS = 30. In word ZAP on TWS with Z on TLS: (30+1+3)×3 = 102 points for a 3-letter word.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Stack multipliers:</span> When a word crosses both TLS and DWS, the letter is tripled first, then the word total is doubled. Letter bonuses always apply before word bonuses.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Cross-word bonus:</span> When your word creates a perpendicular word crossing a premium square, BOTH words get the bonus. This is how parallel plays score so high.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">One-tile premium reach:</span> Extend existing words by one tile to reach a premium square. Hook an S or D onto an existing word that sits near a TWS.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The Triple-Triple — Ultimate Play</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Legendary</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">×9 MULTIPLIER</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">Two TWS squares in one play = word score × 9</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A 7-letter bingo across two TWS squares can score 500+ points in a single turn. These are rare but game-defining moments that tournament players constantly watch for.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">When to Avoid Premium Squares</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Target Premiums When...</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">You have high-value tiles, can score 30+, or when denying your opponent access.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Avoid Premiums When...</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Your play opens a TWS for your opponent with only low-value tiles. A 15-point play that gives away 50 is a net loss.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
